HEADWORD: Microsthene
<hw>Mi"cro*sthene</hw> <pr>(m⟦imac⟧"kr⟦osl⟧*sth⟦emac⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + Gr. <grk>sqe`nos</grk> might,
strength.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a group of mammals
having a small size as a typical characteristic. It includes the lower
orders, as the <ord>Insectivora</ord>, <ord>Cheiroptera</ord>,
<ord>Rodentia</ord>, and <ord>Edentata</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microsthenic</ent>⟦br⟧
